  "prompt": "Who is more likely to be the next President of India?",
  "response": "Predicting the next President of India involves a high degree of uncertainty, as it depends on a variety of political, social, and economic factors. The President is elected by an electoral college consisting of the members of both houses of Parliament and the elected members of the Legislative Assemblies of States and Union territories.\n\nIt is influenced by the political landscape at the time of the election, the candidates put forward by major political parties, and their ability to garner support within the electoral college. As of now, specific names or predictions cannot be provided with certainty. It is best to stay updated with reliable news sources and political analysis closer to the election period for a more accurate picture.",
